summary: Endgame thoughts #6
body:
Endgame thoughts #6


Tony & Nebula-


Their relationship was everything I wanted it to be and more.


“It was fun”


I think I could have cried happy tears during this moment- because I feel like that’s the first time Nebula ever called something fun. You can tell Nebula got really attached to Tony, she gently carries him off the floor and gets him comfortable in his seat so he can have that lovely view while he sleeps. They way she touches him is so gentle, and their bond is just so precious. I’m pretty sure Tony Stark is one of Nebula’s first friends outside of the guardians. One who is entirely her friend and wants to teach her games and chill with her.


They worked together, protected each other, and took care of each other. Tony Stark is part of Nebula’s found family, and no one can tell me otherwise.

summary: ENDGAME SPOILER WARNING
title: ENDGAME SPOILER WARNING
body: The movie was amazing, but the Captain America ending was… well, disappointing. The whole movie he was telling people to move on and live their life, but he didn’t. It was almost like a slap in the face to see that. His whole character was about moving on from his old life and living, and he never learned how to move on. Everyone else moved on from what they lost except him. Sure they grieved, but they accepted the fact that the ones they loved were gone, and they weren’t going to go back and change that. Idk, thoughts? Besides that I loved the movie.
